FBIS3-58993 "drweu016_i_94006" FBIS-WEU-94-016 Document Type:Daily Report 26 Jan 1994 FRANCE Antiterrorist Police Arrest 10 Alleged PKK Supporters AU2501121894 Paris AFP in English 1156 GMT 25 Jan 94 AU2501121894 Paris AFP Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Marseilles, France, Jan 25 (AFP) -- Ten alleged supporters of the Kurdish Workers Party (PKK) were arrested here on Tuesday [25 January] on suspicion of extorting funds for the separatist organisation, which is banned in Turkey. Police, including officers from an antiterrorist unit, carried out the sweep following the arrest of the presumed head of the network on Monday. Police, who searched the homes of the ten, said the PKK contributions were "not always voluntary, violence was often used to get the money."
